# Card Tile (Mandatory)

Full contract: [Card-Tile-Standard.md](../../docs/02_FLUTTER_MIGRATION/Card-Tile-Standard.md)  
Reference: `flutter_app/lib/shared/widgets/vit_compact_product_card.dart`

## When editing strip / tile cards

1. **Tier A only** — `VitCard.height` or `minHeight` + `contentAlign: VitCardContentAlign.center` for horizontal strip tiles only.
2. **Shared widgets** — Use `VitCompactProductCard`, `VitMarketTickerCard`; do not hand-roll fixed-height `VitCard` on pages.
3. **Tokens** — `AppSpacing.cardTilePadding`, `cardTileInnerGap`, module height/width tokens (`homeRecentProductHeight`, etc.).
4. **ListView slot** — Strip `SizedBox` / `ListView` height must match tile height token.
5. **Skeleton parity** — Loading placeholders use the same dimensions as loaded tiles.

## Tiers (short)

| Tier | Fixed height? | Center? | Examples |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| A strip tile | Yes | Yes | Recent product, market ticker |
| B grid tile | Aspect ratio | Internal | `VitServiceTile` |
| C row card | No | No | Next action, discovery |
| D hero | No | No | Portfolio hero |
| E list container | No | No | Market list card |

## Verify before batch complete

```bash
cd flutter_app
dart run tool/card_tile_audit.dart --check --strict-full
dart run tool/card_tile_manifest.dart --check
flutter test test/quality/card_tile_guardrail_test.dart --reporter=compact
```

Exception comment: `// card-tile: allow-start` for documented non-strip fixed minHeight.
